Bitcoin's Academic Pedigree	Paper	How Bitcoin, a radically different proposal for a decentralized cryptocurrency showed that digital cash could be viable.
What is Blockchain Technology? A Step-by-Step Guide For Beginners	Website	A step by step guide that goes into the details of what Blockchain technology is.
Blockchain: The Invisible Technology That's Changing the World	Website	Article that expands on a new immutable digital fabric remaking the internet without people even realizing it. It also shows how Blockchain-based networks, decentralized apps (DApps), and distributed ledgers are becoming the foundation of digital life.
Unspent Transaction Output, UTXO	Website	An online glossary for technical terms regarding Bitcoins. This link Provides the definition and synonyms for an “Unspent Transaction Output”.
Unspent Transaction Output, UTXO	Website	An explanation on how UTXO’s operate vs other methods.
How the NSA identified Satoshi Nakamoto	Website	An article written by Alexander Muse on Medium that explains how the NSA identified the creator of Bitcoin, Satoshi Nakamoto.
How a Bitcoin Transaction Works	Website	This article explains what a bitcoin transaction is, its purpose and outcome. The explanation in this article is suitable for both novice and intermediate bitcoin users.
